.TH ANTS-TERMINAL 1 "2026-04-15" "ants-terminal 0.6.24" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
ants-terminal \- modern, themeable terminal emulator with GPU rendering and Lua plugins
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ants-terminal
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ants-terminal
is a Qt6 terminal emulator written from scratch in C++20.
It includes a custom VT100/xterm escape-sequence parser, a PTY driver
backed by
.BR forkpty (3),
hardware-accelerated rendering via
.BR QOpenGLWidget
(with an optional glyph-atlas GLSL renderer), inline graphics
(Sixel / Kitty / iTerm2), eleven built-in color themes, an
OpenAI-compatible AI assistant pane, an SSH bookmark manager, and an
optional sandboxed Lua 5.4 plugin system.
.PP
With no options, it launches a single window running the user's login
shell (the
.B SHELL
environment variable, falling back to
.IR /bin/bash )
inside a fresh PTY.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display a short usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the program version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-quake ", " \-\-dropdown
Run in
.I Quake
/ drop-down mode: the window is pinned to the top of the active screen,
spans its full width, occupies one third of the available height, and
slides in and out of view via the configured global hotkey. Useful as a
desktop-wide always-available scratch terminal.
.TP
.BI \-\-new\-plugin " NAME"
Scaffold a new Lua plugin in the user's plugin directory and exit
without launching a window.
.I NAME
must match
.RB [ A\-Za\-z ][ A\-Za\-z0\-9_\- ]{0,63}.
The command creates
.IR ~/.config/ants\-terminal/plugins/NAME/
containing
.IR init.lua ,
.IR manifest.json ,
and a starter
.IR README.md .
The plugin is created disabled; enable it under
Settings \(-> Plugins or by adding the name to
.I enabled_plugins
in
.IR config.json .
See
.B PLUGINS.md
in the source tree for the full
.B ants.*
API reference.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SHELL
Path of the login shell to spawn under the PTY. Falls back to
.I /bin/bash
when unset.
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate per-user state (config, themes, plugins, sessions) when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
and
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
are unset.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Per-user configuration root. Ants Terminal stores its config under
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/ants\-terminal/
(default
.IR ~/.config/ants\-terminal/ ).
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Per-user runtime data root. Ants Terminal stores sessions, recordings,
and logs under
.IR $XDG_DATA_HOME/ants\-terminal/
(default
.IR ~/.local/share/ants\-terminal/ ).
.TP
.B ANTS_PLUGIN_DEV
When set to
.BR 1 ,
the Lua plugin manager logs verbosely on load and reload, and the
plugin directory is watched so edits to
.I init.lua
take effect without restarting the terminal. Intended for plugin
authors only.
.TP
.B QT_QPA_PLATFORM
Standard Qt platform-abstraction selector. Set to
.B offscreen
when running headless (CI, sanitizer smoke tests).
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/ants-terminal/config.json
Persistent configuration. Mode
.B 0600.
Created on first run with defaults; edited live when changed via
Settings.
.TP
.I ~/.config/ants-terminal/themes/*.json
Optional user theme files. Each defines a theme name plus the 16-color
ANSI palette and default foreground / background colors. Picked up at
startup.
.TP
.I ~/.config/ants-terminal/plugins/<name>/
Lua plugin directory created by
.BR \-\-new\-plugin .
Each plugin contains
.IR init.lua ,
.IR manifest.json ,
and an optional
.IR README.md .
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ants-terminal/sessions/
Compressed binary snapshots of scrollback and screen state, written
when
.B session_persistence
is enabled in the config.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ants-terminal/recordings/
Saved terminal recordings (input + output stream).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/ants-terminal/logs/
Per-session log files written by Settings \(-> Logging.
.TP
.I <project>/audit_rules.json
Optional per-project rule pack consumed by the in-app Project Audit
dialog. Appends to or overrides the built-in rule set; supports
.IR path_rules
for glob-based severity shifts.
.TP
.I <project>/.audit_suppress
JSONL suppression list (v2:
.I {key, rule, reason, timestamp}
per line) for the Project Audit dialog. v1 plain-key lines are still
loaded and rewritten on the first save.
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit \(em either the GUI session ended cleanly or
.BR \-\-help / \-\-version / \-\-new\-plugin
completed.
.TP
.B 2
.BR \-\-new\-plugin :
the plugin name failed validation.
.TP
.B 3
.BR \-\-new\-plugin :
a plugin with that name already exists.
.TP
.B 4
.BR \-\-new\-plugin :
could not create the plugin directory.
.TP
.B 5
.BR \-\-new\-plugin :
could not write one of the scaffolded files.
.
